Navigate to the Claude Code settings page and systematically revoke all active authorization token sessions. Use the following approach which was proven to work correctly:

1. Start at https://claude.ai/settings/claude-code and wait for the page to fully load
2. Identify all "Revoke access" buttons (aria-label="Revoke access") in the Authorization tokens section
3. For each session, execute these steps in sequence:
   a. Get the first revoke button (btn[0]) and find its parent TR row element
   b. Call the button's React onClick handler directly via: Object.keys(btn).find(k => k.startsWith('__reactProps'))[btn]['onClick']({ preventDefault: () => {}, stopPropagation: () => {}, target: btn, currentTarget: btn })
   c. Wait for the confirmation dialog to appear (check every 80ms for up to 2.5 seconds)
   d. Find the "Revoke Access" confirm button in the dialog
   e. Call its React onClick handler the same way as step b
   f. Wait 150ms for the click to register
   g. IMMEDIATELY remove the parent TR row from DOM using row.remove() - this is critical to avoid re-targeting the same revoked session
   h. Wait for the dialog to close (check every 60ms for up to 2 seconds)
   i. Wait 50ms before proceeding to the next session
4. Repeat until no more revoke buttons remain in the DOM
5. Track progress with a live overlay showing: revoked count, remaining count (decreasing), rate/min, and error count (should stay at 0)
6. Each revoked row must be visually removed from the page to prevent clicking it twice

CRITICAL LESSONS from testing:
- Do NOT use .click() on buttons positioned at x=1656 (off-screen from virtual scrolling) - use React's onClick directly
- Do NOT skip the DOM removal step - the website doesn't update its UI after revoke, so you MUST manually remove rows to move to the next session
- Do NOT assume btn[0] is a different session after revoke - it will be the SAME session unless you remove its row from DOM
- Always call the confirm button via React onClick as well, not just the revoke button
- The virtual scroll may render 628 buttons visible but only ~500-600 are actual remaining sessions due to virtual scroll overscan

Expected behavior:
- Rate should be 100-120 sessions per minute
- Errors should remain at 0 throughout
- Remaining count should steadily decrease (628 → 545 → 474 → etc.)
- Duration for ~600 sessions should be approximately 5-6 minutes < edit the sessions based on the amount you see in the page> this was just an estimate. 
- Progress indicator shows "#N revoked & removed" for each session
